## One more improvement

Currently you have:

```java
catch (Exception e) {
    throw new TechnicalException(
            "Unable to load user from partner repository");
}
```

This is too broad.

If `exchangeToken()` fails, or JWT parsing fails, or Redis fails, you'll still get:

> Unable to load user from partner repository

which is misleading.

I'd change it to:

```java
catch (TechnicalException e) {
    throw e;
}
catch (Exception e) {
    log.error("Authentication callback failed", e);
    throw new TechnicalException("Authentication callback failed");
}
```

This preserves your specific errors like:

* Missing access_token
* Missing id_token
* Invalid state
* App config not found

instead of masking everything behind one generic message.

These changes will make Fortify, Sonar, and operational debugging much happier.

